[@mikey](@6ilZq3kN0F+dXFHAPjAwMm87JEb/VdB+LC9eIMW3sa0=.ed25519) 

You did the thing! That's actually super cool, are there any clients that accept input like that and open a specific message? I might try and get this working on the web -- I think all I'd need is a way to start/stop services and then a URI handler that proxies from https://localhost/ssb:message:sha256:abcdef to the correct service:

```json
{
  "services": {
    "patchfoo": "http://localhost:8027/%s",
    "git-ssb-web": "http://localhost:7718/%s",
    "some-dat-proxy-maybe": "http://localhost:1234/%s"
  },
  "handlers": {
    "ssb": "patchfoo",
    "ssb?type=git": "git-ssb-web",
    "dat": "some-dat-proxy-maybe"
  }
}
```

Super excited to try out your spike!
